The paper discusses the implementation of an all-optical diffractive deep neural network (D2NN) architecture for image classification and imaging lens function. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the potential applications in robotics (cs.RO), information theory (cs.IT), optics (cs.OH), and multimedia (cs.MM).
